28/09/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A two-day regional conference on co-operation in fighting organised crime opens in Belgrade on Monday (September 28th). 
European Commission Vice President responsible for Justice, Freedom and Security Jacques Barrot will attend the forum, along with justice and interior ministers of Balkan countries and representatives of Italy and Hungary. 
Serbian Interior Minister Ivica Dacic says the meeting provides Belgrade the chance to represent itself as a regional leader in co-operation in the fields of interior affairs and justice. 
As for Barrot's participation, Dacic said it presents an opportunity for Belgrade to demonstrate its progress in meeting the EU-set benchmarks towards scrapping visas for Serbian citizens. 
(Beta, Tanjug, RTS - 27/09/09)
